<subSubSection id="3ED405AB91365F8C5CFBB237BFA6D062" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="typification">
<paragraph id="4F40555316BF68FA4B57F063644C83B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Typification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="05839D64C945F7645A05E9025801F5A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
In choosing a lectotype for this species, we have selected the only extant 
<emphasis id="3F470090991E97987F2BA7773BD013B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Tweedie</emphasis>
collection. No suitable material was found at B, BR or M.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B9FA5730E9A6BD306B57A2D1B9BADB14" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="340475CA091B056AA19A72DB97007AD0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B151EFA089EFCC7BCF991C15B126C9F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This species is characterised by the inflorescence that consists of long-pedunculate, usually 3-flowered cymes and by the large ovate leaves, pubescent to subtomentose on both surfaces.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
